r Xa","Inhibition of tissue factor pathway","Antithrombin-mediated inhibition of thrombin","Vitamin K epoxide reductase inhibition"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EFondaparinux works through \u003Cstrong\u003Eantithrombin-mediated inhibition of factor Xa\u003C/strong\u003E. It binds specifically to antithrombin to significantly increase antithrombin-mediated inhibition of factor Xa. Due to its small size it has no effect on thrombin activity. \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDirect binding to factor Xa\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect as fondaparinux requires antithrombin as a cofactor to exert its anticoagulant effect\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EInhibition of tissue factor pathway\u003C/strong\u003E is not the mechanism as fondaparinux does not interact with the tissue factor pathway\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAntithrombin-mediated inhibition of thrombin\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect as fondaparinux\u0027s pentasaccharide structure is too small to bridge antithrombin to thrombin\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EVitamin K epoxide reductase inhibition\u003C/strong\u003E describes the mechanism of action of warfarin, not fondaparinux\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe selective anti-Xa activity of fondaparinux results in predictable pharmacokinetics and eliminates the need for routine coagulation monitoring in most patients.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Fondaparinux is a synthetic pentasaccharide that selectively binds to antithrombin to inhibit factor Xa.","Unlike heparins, fondaparinux has no direct effect on thrombin due to its small size.","Fondaparinux has highly selective anti-Xa activity and predictable pharmacokinetics."],"references":["Therapeutic Guidelines. Melbourne: Therapeutic Guidelines Limited. Available from: https://www.tg.org.au","Ritter J, Flower RJ (Rod J), Henderson G (Graeme), et al.\u00a0Rang and Dale\u2019s Pharmacology. Tenth edition. Elsevier; 2024.","Australian Medicines Handbook\u00a0(online). Adelaide: Australian Medicines Handbook Pty Ltd. Available from:\u00a0https://amhonline.amh.net.au/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"62767"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17129"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"62767","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/62767"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-06T14:57:47+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-06T14:58:06+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9819"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"77260"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"7"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCoun